      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hello!\n\nThis PR adds a way for the config.ini file to specify a default hinge angle for each posture. This can be added as a third value in the hw.sensor.hinge_angles_posture_definitions config.\n\nRationale is possible need for posture definition to specify a different default value from the current calculation [(start_angle + end_angle) / 2.0]. This default value is used when using the UI posture buttons to quickly jump between postures.\n\nWithout this patch: posture config can only be e.g. 120-360, with default hinge value for that posture being automatically set to (120+360)/2\nWith this patch: a posture config of 120-360 is still possible and will have the same auto-calculation as before. a posture config of 120-360-120 translates to a posture between 120 and 360 degrees, with the default value being 120 degrees.\n\nThank you for considering this PR.",
